[WHIMPERS]

1491
01:45:00,002 --> 01:45:03,921
My man, my man, my man.
What's this thing
with all these numbers?

1492
01:45:04,172 --> 01:45:06,215
[###]

1493
01:45:09,678 --> 01:45:11,721
It's-- It's--

1494
01:45:11,888 --> 01:45:13,723
No, no, no, no.

1495
01:45:13,932 --> 01:45:15,558
Because if it was a bomb,

1496
01:45:15,726 --> 01:45:19,312
the alarms would go off
because all these hotels
have bomb detectors. Right?

1497
01:45:19,479 --> 01:45:21,814
[ALARM BUZZING]

1498
01:45:21,982 --> 01:45:23,983
WOMAN [ON LOUDSPEAKER]:
This is a Type A alert.

1499
01:45:24,151 --> 01:45:27,862
For security reasons,
the hotel must be evacuated.

1500
01:45:29,072 --> 01:45:30,740
Please proceed calmly
to the lifeboats

1501
01:45:30,949 --> 01:45:32,366
Stay calm !

1502
01:45:32,534 --> 01:45:34,076
located in the main hallways.

1503
01:45:34,244 --> 01:45:35,411
Please, stay calm !

1504
01:45:35,579 --> 01:45:37,496
[CROWD SCREAMING]

1505
01:45:41,084 --> 01:45:43,753
Korben. Korben, my man,
you know how to stop this, right?

1506
01:45:45,881 --> 01:45:47,506
Korben?

1507
01:45:49,468 --> 01:45:52,762
WOMAN [ON LOUDSPEAKER]:
Two minutes to complete evacuation.

1508
01:45:54,765 --> 01:45:57,600
Get back!
Evacuation ! Evacuation !

1509
01:45:57,768 --> 01:46:01,103
Sorry, sir, you can't stay here.
There's a bomb in the hotel.

1510
01:46:06,068 --> 01:46:07,234
I know.

1511
01:46:09,613 --> 01:46:11,364
[CROWD SCREAMING]

1512
01:46:22,209 --> 01:46:25,002
RUBY: I don't want to die.
Please, my son.

1513
01:46:25,629 --> 01:46:26,962
Get in. Get in.

1514
01:46:31,802 --> 01:46:34,553
WOMAN [ON LOUDSPEAKER]:
One minute to total evacuation.

1515
01:46:39,017 --> 01:46:40,309
This one.

1516
01:46:43,730 --> 01:46:45,564
Forty-five seconds.

1517
01:46:48,819 --> 01:46:50,403
KORBEN:
Get her strapped in.

1518
01:46:55,325 --> 01:46:58,160
Korben, Korben. Korben, my man,
you know how to fly this thing?

1519
01:46:58,328 --> 01:46:59,620
Just like driving a cab.

1520
01:46:59,996 --> 01:47:02,081
[ENGINE WHIRRING]

1521
01:47:04,251 --> 01:47:06,168
But the door?
How we gonna get out the door?

1522
01:47:19,683 --> 01:47:21,517
Fifteen seconds.

1523
01:47:26,273 --> 01:47:29,859
Ten, nine, eight,

1524
01:47:30,026 --> 01:47:34,447
seven, six, five...

1525
01:47:38,368 --> 01:47:39,869
[GRUNTS]

1526
01:47:40,620 --> 01:47:42,079
[BEEPING]

1527
01:47:51,214 --> 01:47:53,132
For the honour.

1528
01:47:54,593 --> 01:47:56,051
[TICKING]

1529
01:47:57,137 --> 01:47:58,220
Oh, no.

1530
01:47:58,889 --> 01:48:00,139
You should hold on.

1531
01:48:13,153 --> 01:48:14,320
Come on.

1532
01:48:22,496 --> 01:48:23,746
Like driving a cab.

1533
01:48:25,749 --> 01:48:28,417
Ladies and gentlemen,
it is now 7 p. m. Time for the news.

1534
01:48:28,585 --> 01:48:30,503
See you tomorrow
for a new adventure.

1535
01:48:30,921 --> 01:48:32,588
MAN [ON EARPIECE]:
End of transmission.

1536
01:48:33,507 --> 01:48:35,508
That's the best show I ever did.

1537
01:48:38,428 --> 01:48:41,180
Mr. President, Major Dallas
has the five elements on board,

1538
01:48:41,348 --> 01:48:44,099
and the priest is guiding them
directly to the temple.

1539
01:48:45,060 --> 01:48:47,144
[###]

1540
01:48:48,688 --> 01:48:50,022
We're saved.

1541
01:49:06,206 --> 01:49:08,874
The diva said that
I should take care of you.

1542
01:49:09,960 --> 01:49:12,545
Humans act so strange.

1543
01:49:12,712 --> 01:49:13,879
What do you mean?

1544
01:49:15,549 --> 01:49:17,591
Everything you created

1545
01:49:17,759 --> 01:49:19,385
is used to destroy.

1546
01:49:19,761 --> 01:49:21,428
Yeah.

1547
01:49:21,638 --> 01:49:25,307
We call it human nature.
You learn about that on your screen?

1548
01:49:25,475 --> 01:49:28,310
I'm not finished yet.
I'm up to V.

1549
01:49:29,145 --> 01:49:30,479
V is good.

1550
01:49:30,897 --> 01:49:32,773
Some very good words in V.

1551
01:49:32,941 --> 01:49:34,233
Like what?

1552
01:49:36,570 --> 01:49:37,903
Valiant.

1553
01:49:38,405 --> 01:49:39,738
Vulnerable.

1554
01:49:42,158 --> 01:49:43,826
Very beautiful.

1555
01:49:49,249 --> 01:49:51,500
[CHEERING]

1556
01:49:55,589 --> 01:49:58,090
PRESIDENT:
Oh, of course, Munro!

1557
01:49:59,426 --> 01:50:01,927
Mr. President?
Yes, now what?

1558
01:50:02,178 --> 01:50:03,971
l-- l--

1559
01:50:05,265 --> 01:50:06,682
We have a problem.

1560
01:50:12,188 --> 01:50:13,522
What do you mean
it's advancing?

1561
01:50:13,690 --> 01:50:17,276
It's not only advancing,
it's moving at incredible speed.
We're having trouble following it.

1562
01:50:21,781 --> 01:50:25,117
And do you have any idea
where it's heading?

1563
01:50:25,869 --> 01:50:28,495
[###]

1564
01:50:31,958 --> 01:50:34,877
Korben, there's a general
on the phone.

1565
01:50:35,712 --> 01:50:37,838
I'll give you to the president.

1566
01:50:38,548 --> 01:50:41,467
Major Dallas, I first would like
to salute a warrior.

1567
01:50:41,635 --> 01:50:43,344
You're a shining example
of this army's might.

1568
01:50:43,511 --> 01:50:45,220
Mr. President. Mr. President.
In the name of the Federation

1569
01:50:45,388 --> 01:50:46,889
and its territories--
Any idea when you're gonna be

1570
01:50:47,057 --> 01:50:48,140
getting to the point?

1571
01:50:50,518 --> 01:50:55,314
Okay. There's a ball of fire
1200 miles in diameter
heading straight for Earth,

1572
01:50:55,482 --> 01:50:58,817
and we have no idea how
to stop it. That's the problem.

1573
01:51:02,155 --> 01:51:03,656
How much time do we have?

1574
01:51:04,658 --> 01:51:08,160
If its speed remains constant,
in an hour and 57 minutes.

1575
01:51:09,245 --> 01:51:11,246
I'll call you back in two hours.

1576
01:51:11,414 --> 01:51:14,333
Hello? Hello? Hello?

1577
01:51:16,586 --> 01:51:18,420
[###]

1578
01:52:24,154 --> 01:52:26,113
They just landed in the desert.

1579
01:52:28,366 --> 01:52:30,033
CORNELIUS:
Good job, David.

1580
01:52:31,745 --> 01:52:33,996
Put her in the centre.
Where? Here?

1581
01:52:41,755 --> 01:52:43,505
You got it figured out, Father?

1582
01:52:43,673 --> 01:52:46,258
This one should be fire.

1583
01:52:46,509 --> 01:52:48,343
You know how all this works?
Theoretically, yes.

1584
01:52:48,511 --> 01:52:51,972
Theoretically?
The four stones should go around.

1585
01:52:52,140 --> 01:52:54,183
The fifth element should be
in the middle,

1586
01:52:54,350 --> 01:52:57,186
and then the weapon
against evil should work.

1587
01:52:57,854 --> 01:52:59,396
You've never seen this
work before, have you?

1588
01:52:59,564 --> 01:53:01,148
No.

1589
01:53:01,357 --> 01:53:04,777
Every weapon has a manual.
I'm sure this has one too.

1590
01:53:13,077 --> 01:53:15,871
That's it. That's it.
Match up the symbols. Go! Go!

1591
01:53:17,540 --> 01:53:18,582
Wind.

1592
01:53:20,418 --> 01:53:22,503
My man, what you doing?

1593
01:53:22,670 --> 01:53:24,588
What?
What you doing?

1594
01:53:25,799 --> 01:53:27,591
Trying to keep you
in the DJ business.

1595
01:53:31,304 --> 01:53:32,387
Fire.

1596
01:53:33,848 --> 01:53:34,932
Done.

1597
01:53:35,099 --> 01:53:38,936
So, what happens now?
So now, we have to open them.

1598
01:53:40,063 --> 01:53:43,440
And you know how to do that, right?
Theoretically...

1599
01:53:45,235 --> 01:53:46,318
no.
No.

1600
01:53:51,115 --> 01:53:53,867
Leeloo, wake up, honey, wake up.
You have to help us.

1601
01:53:54,035 --> 01:53:56,912
Leeloo. How do you open
these stones?

1602
01:53:58,122 --> 01:54:00,082
Wind blows.

1603
01:54:01,584 --> 01:54:03,126
Fire burns.

1604
01:54:03,336 --> 01:54:06,630
Yes, I know all that.
But how do you open these stones?

1605
01:54:06,965 --> 01:54:08,257
Rain...

1606
01:54:11,636 --> 01:54:13,095
falls.

1607
01:54:16,599 --> 01:54:18,225
Leeloo. Leeloo.

1608
01:54:19,602 --> 01:54:20,936
What does it mean?

1609
01:54:22,772 --> 01:54:24,106
I think that--

1610
01:54:24,274 --> 01:54:25,607
Maybe it's a charade.
What?

1611
01:54:25,775 --> 01:54:27,109
A game or something.

1612
01:54:27,485 --> 01:54:29,945
If we don't get these stones open
in five minutes, we're all dead.

1613
01:54:30,113 --> 01:54:31,780
Dead?
Yes, dead.

1614
01:54:44,377 --> 01:54:45,669
Too late.

1615
01:54:47,463 --> 01:54:50,632
We've lost contact with them.
Three minutes.

1616
01:54:52,135 --> 01:54:55,137
I think mine is broken.
Why I gotta get the broke one?

1617
01:55:03,646 --> 01:55:05,314
We're never gonna make it.

1618
01:55:06,482 --> 01:55:08,650
[SIGHS]

1619
01:55:10,278 --> 01:55:12,821
Korben. Korben, it moved !

1620
01:55:14,282 --> 01:55:15,657
What'd you do?
Show me what you did.

1621
01:55:15,825 --> 01:55:18,160
Nothing.
Shut up, shut up!

1622
01:55:18,328 --> 01:55:21,288
Shut up! Calm down. Show me
what you did. Take me through it,
step by step.

1623
01:55:21,456 --> 01:55:23,665
I was just standing here like this.
Quickly.

1624
01:55:23,833 --> 01:55:28,170
Okay, and I put my hands on
the top like this, and I said:

1625
01:55:29,047 --> 01:55:31,006
"We're not gonna make it."

1626
01:55:32,675 --> 01:55:33,926
That's it?

1627
01:55:36,554 --> 01:55:37,971
[SIGHS]

1628
01:55:42,685 --> 01:55:44,019
RUBY:
Korben, my man.

1629
01:55:44,687 --> 01:55:46,146
Wind.

1630
01:55:46,564 --> 01:55:48,857
She said, "Wind-- Wind blows."

1631
01:55:51,361 --> 01:55:53,820
[BLOWING]

1632
01:55:56,741 --> 01:55:58,241
Everyone take a stone.

1633
01:55:58,576 --> 01:56:01,536
Water for water. Fire for fire.
Earth for earth. Go, now!

1634
01:56:03,957 --> 01:56:05,082
Earth.

1635
01:56:05,375 --> 01:56:06,875
Open the other one.
Okay...

1636
01:56:20,098 --> 01:56:22,265
K-- Korben.

1637
01:56:22,725 --> 01:56:25,102
Korben, my man, I have no fire.

1638
01:56:25,269 --> 01:56:27,437
I have no matches.
Do you have any matches?

1639
01:56:27,605 --> 01:56:30,065
I stopped smoking. If I knew--
I mean-- Father, you smoke?

1640
01:56:30,233 --> 01:56:32,901
Got some matches? Matches?
We need some fire.

1641
01:56:34,195 --> 01:56:35,904
We all gonna die.

1642
01:56:43,121 --> 01:56:44,579
Don't breathe.

1643
01:56:50,878 --> 01:56:52,587
[GASPING]

1644
01:56:55,091 --> 01:56:56,758
[RUBY WHIMPERS]

1645
01:57:03,808 --> 01:57:04,933
Fire.

1646
01:57:05,643 --> 01:57:06,727
One minute.

1647
01:57:06,894 --> 01:57:08,437
KORBEN:
Let's go. Let's go. Leeloo.

1648
01:57:08,604 --> 01:57:11,648
Wake up. Wake up.
It's time for you to work now.

1649
01:57:12,442 --> 01:57:13,942
Protect life...

1650
01:57:15,153 --> 01:57:16,445
until death.

1651
01:57:16,612 --> 01:57:19,448
No, no, Leeloo! Listen to me!
Listen to me. Listen.

1652
01:57:19,615 --> 01:57:22,284
Listen, I know you're very tired.
I know you're very tired.

1653
01:57:22,452 --> 01:57:26,163
I'll take you on a vacation when
we're done. I swear, a real vacation.
A real vacation, just you and me.

1654
01:57:26,456 --> 01:57:29,791
But listen to me, if you don't do
something right now, we're all
gonna die. You understand?

1655
01:57:29,959 --> 01:57:33,628
What's the use of saving life
when you see what you do with it?

1656
01:57:33,963 --> 01:57:36,631
It'll be entering the atmosphere
in 40 seconds.

1657
01:57:38,051 --> 01:57:39,634
KORBEN: Leeloo, you're right.
You're right, you're right.

1658
01:57:39,802 --> 01:57:41,636
But there are some things,

1659
01:57:41,804 --> 01:57:44,473
very nice things worth saving,
some beautiful things.

1660
01:57:44,849 --> 01:57:46,683
Beautiful things.

1661
01:57:47,810 --> 01:57:49,269
Like love?

1662
01:57:49,437 --> 01:57:51,438
Yes, love.
That's good. That's good.

1663
01:57:51,606 --> 01:57:53,982
That's a good example.
Like love. Love is worth saving.

1664
01:57:54,859 --> 01:57:59,988
I don't know love.

1665
01:58:00,156 --> 01:58:02,491
I was built to protect,
not to love.

1666
01:58:02,700 --> 01:58:05,494
So there's no use for me
other than this.

1667
01:58:05,661 --> 01:58:08,121
No, no, no, you're wrong.
You're wrong. You're wrong.

1668
01:58:08,831 --> 01:58:11,833
I need you. I need you, very much.

1669
01:58:13,586 --> 01:58:14,711
Why?

1670
01:58:16,672 --> 01:58:19,716
Because...

1671
01:58:20,676 --> 01:58:22,677
Tell her, Korben.

1672
01:58:24,514 --> 01:58:27,182
Tell me. Please.

1673
01:58:27,350 --> 01:58:29,226
Why do you need me?

1674
01:58:29,727 --> 01:58:32,854
Because...
Tell me.

1675
01:58:35,024 --> 01:58:36,483
Tell me.
Because l--

1676
01:58:36,692 --> 01:58:38,193
Because I love you.

1677
01:58:39,403 --> 01:58:40,737
I love you.

1678
01:58:44,659 --> 01:58:48,912
Ten, nine, eight, seven,

1679
01:58:49,372 --> 01:58:52,874
six, five, four, three,

1680
01:58:53,251 --> 01:58:55,627
two, one.

1681
01:59:05,346 --> 01:59:07,639
[YELLING]

1682
01:59:16,065 --> 01:59:18,191
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1683
01:59:18,359 --> 01:59:20,026
[###]

1684
01:59:33,666 --> 01:59:37,794
MAN [ON RADIN]:
Scanner imaging has confirmed
the dark planet: dead.

1685
01:59:38,462 --> 01:59:41,256
The planet seems to have stopped
at 62 miles from impact.

1686
01:59:45,761 --> 01:59:47,304
[LAUGHS]

1687
01:59:52,894 --> 01:59:54,227
Yes!

1688
01:59:54,395 --> 01:59:56,479
What's wrong with you?
What you screaming for?

1689
01:59:56,689 --> 01:59:58,982
Every five minutes,
it's something.
A bomb or something.

1690
01:59:59,192 --> 02:00:01,610
I'm leaving. Bzz!

1691
02:00:03,946 --> 02:00:06,281
[SIRENS BLARING]

1692
02:00:06,574 --> 02:00:08,742
[PRESIDENT LAUGHING]

1693
02:00:15,124 --> 02:00:16,416
Mr. President.

1694
02:00:16,584 --> 02:00:19,294
Let me introduce you to
Professor Mactilburgh
who runs the centre.

1695
02:00:19,462 --> 02:00:21,254
It's an honour to receive you,
Mr. President.

1696
02:00:21,422 --> 02:00:23,089
Yes, well...
Where are my two heroes?

1697
02:00:23,257 --> 02:00:27,010
Oh, they were so tired from their
ordeal, we put them in the reactor
this morning.

1698
02:00:27,220 --> 02:00:29,137
I have 19 more meetings
after this one, professor.

1699
02:00:29,305 --> 02:00:31,681
Yeah. I'm sorry.
Let me see if they're revived.

1700
02:00:31,849 --> 02:00:32,974
Thank you.

1701
02:00:33,226 --> 02:00:34,643
We go live in one minute,
Mr. President.

1702
02:00:34,810 --> 02:00:36,311
Mm-hm.

1703
02:00:42,109 --> 02:00:43,485
Ah...

1704
02:00:43,653 --> 02:00:45,153
They're...

1705
02:00:46,364 --> 02:00:48,281
not ready.

1706
02:00:48,449 --> 02:00:49,699
They need...

1707
02:00:49,867 --> 02:00:52,661
five more minutes.
You have 20 seconds.

1708
02:00:52,828 --> 02:00:54,996
No, ma'am. No, no,
I tried. No, ma'am.

1709
02:00:55,164 --> 02:00:56,289
Who's that?

1710
02:00:56,457 --> 02:00:57,999
Some woman. Claims
to be Korben's mother.

1711
02:00:58,167 --> 02:00:59,960
Well, give it here.

1712
02:01:00,503 --> 02:01:05,173
Mrs. Dallas, this is the president.
On behalf of the Federation--

1713
02:01:05,341 --> 02:01:07,342
MRS. DALLAS [ON PHONE]:
Oh, please, that doesn't even
sound like him.

1714
02:01:07,510 --> 02:01:09,678
The president's an idiot.
You don't sound like an idiot.

1715
02:01:09,845 --> 02:01:13,056
If you don't want to talk
to your mother, just avoid me
like usual, huh?

1716
02:01:13,266 --> 02:01:16,726
I'll just throw myself in traffic.
I'll just Saran Wrap myself to the bed
and pretend my child...

1717
02:01:16,894 --> 02:01:18,812
[MRS. DALLAS
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1718
02:01:19,021 --> 02:01:21,898
[R.X. R.A.'S "THE LITTLE LIGHT
OF LOVE" PLAYS]

